Be it enacted by the Council as follows:
	Section 1. Subdivision 1 of section 3-703 of the administrative code of the city of New York is amended to add a new paragraph (p), to read as follows:
      (p) not have been convicted, provided such conviction has not been vacated pursuant to the criminal procedure law or pardoned by the governor pursuant to section 4 of article IV of the New York state constitution, of a felony defined in:
      (i) article 200 of the penal law;
      (ii) article 496 of the penal law;
      (iii) sections 155.30, 155.35, 155.40, and 155.42 of the penal law, if in connection to public funds;
      (iv) sections 175.10, 175.25 and 175.35 of the penal law; if in connection to public funds;
      (v) section 195.20 of the penal law;
      (vi) section 666 of title 18 of the United States code;
      (vii) sections 1341, 1343 and 1346 of title 18 of the United States code; and
      (viii) any felony attempt or conspiracy to commit any of the aforementioned felonies.
      ï¿½ 2. This local law takes effect immediately.

